# Unity Patterns

## MonoBehaviour Lifecycle

Follow this established order in all MonoBehaviours:

1. **`Awake`** — Cache component refs (`GetComponent`), set singleton `Instance`
2. **`Start`** — Read prefs, subscribe to events, initial state
3. **`OnEnable` / `OnDisable`** — Register/unregister from static registries (`RtsSimRegistry`, `ProductionBuilding.All`)
4. **`Update` / `LateUpdate`** — Simulation tick, UI sync
5. **`OnDestroy`** — Clear singleton if `Instance == this`, unsubscribe events

## Singleton Pattern

Used extensively. Follow this exact pattern:

```csharp
public static MySystem Instance { get; private set; }

void Awake()
{
    Instance = this;
}

void OnDestroy()
{
    if (Instance == this) Instance = null;
}
```

Do NOT use `DontDestroyOnLoad` — all singletons are scene-scoped.

## Registry Pattern

For types that need fast iteration without `FindObjectsByType`:

```csharp
static readonly List<MyType> s_all = new();
public static IReadOnlyList<MyType> All => s_all;

void OnEnable() => s_all.Add(this);
void OnDisable() => s_all.Remove(this);
```

Examples: `RtsSimRegistry` (units + fruit), `ProductionBuilding.All`, `TerrainFeatureRegistry`.

## NavMesh

- `NavMeshSurface` on the world root, baked at runtime by `SkirmishDirector`
- Units require `NavMeshAgent` (`[RequireComponent]` on `InsectUnit`)
- Obstacles use `NavMeshObstacle` with carving (clay, fruit, hive, rocky ridges)
- Use `NavMesh.SamplePosition` for spawn and building placement validation

## UI Construction

UI is built **programmatically at runtime** (not prefab-based):
- `Canvas` + `CanvasScaler` (1920x1080 reference resolution, `ScaleWithScreenSize`)
- `InputSystemUIInputModule` on `EventSystem`
- Legacy `Text` component (not TextMeshPro)
- `GameHUD` creates the root canvas; `Sc2BottomBar` builds the full RTS chrome underneath
- Static `RectTransform` refs (`GameHUD.HudCanvasRect`, `MapPanel`, etc.) let other systems parent under the shared canvas

## Input

Uses **New Input System** but via **direct device polling** (not Input Action assets in code):
- `Mouse.current.leftButton`, `Mouse.current.position`, `Keyboard.current.escapeKey`, etc.
- `EventSystem.current.IsPointerOverGameObject()` to block world clicks when over UI

## Editor Helpers

Use `#if UNITY_EDITOR` blocks for convenience auto-wiring:

```csharp
#if UNITY_EDITOR
void OnValidate()
{
    if (someSprite == null)
        someSprite = UnityEditor.AssetDatabase.LoadAssetAtPath<Sprite>("Assets/...");
}
#endif
```

## Performance Conventions

- Static shared meshes/materials for selection rings (created once, reused)
- Static `Collider[]` buffers for `Physics.OverlapSphere` (no per-frame allocation)
- Material tint caches (`Dictionary<Color, Material>`) to avoid runtime material instantiation
- `RtsSimRegistry` avoids per-frame `FindObjectsByType`
